[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Have you ever lost hours writing retry logic, cron jobs, [music] and brittle state machines just to keep a long-running process alive for when something inevitably fails? Let\'s discover Temporal, a free open source durable execution platform that lets you'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'write code as if failure didn\'t exist. You write your business logic as normal code in your favorite language such as Go, TypeScript, Python, and Temporal automatically save the state of every'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'step. If a service [music] crashes, the network drops, or an API times out, your workflow just pick up exactly where it left [music] off with no loss progress and no manual recovery. It\'s the'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'backbone behind reliable payments, order processing, and long-running jobs, and increasingly the AI agents at companies like OpenAI, Replit, and Cursor. To start using Temporal, you can use other'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'cloud version with the essentials plan starting at $100 per month up to 1 million actions or apply to get free credits. You can self-deploy it for free by following the guide in the official documentation or use a platform like'

